com/business/2013/dec/31/debenhams-shares-christmas-trading-profit-warning\" title=\"\">post-Christmas profits warning</a> from department store chain Debenhams.</p><p>The British Retail Consortium said shop prices fell for the eighth month running in December. The fall of 0.8% on a year earlier was the deepest deflation since the data began in December 2006.</p><p>The fall in overall shop prices came as non-food prices fell an annual 2.3% in December compared with deflation of 2% in November, according to the monthly data compiled with Nielsen.</p><p>Food prices continued to rise but at the slowest pace for more than three years. As fresh fruit prices fell and those for non-alcoholic drinks barely rose, food inflation eased to 1.7% from a rate of 2.3% in November.</p><p>The numbers echo reports from the high street of heavy discounting in the run-up to Christmas, particularly on clothes. Debenhams <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2014/jan/02/debenhams-finance-boss-quits-christmas-profit-warning\" title=\"\">parted company with its finance director</a> last week after it warned of a sharp fall in profits. Investors are nervous about the prospects for Marks &amp; Spencer, which reports on Thursday, after it too <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2013/dec/18/marks-and-spencer-debenhams-slump-share-price\" title=\"\">slashed prices in a last-minute attempt to woo shoppers</a> before Christmas. Rival Next held out against the wave of discounting and <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2014/jan/03/next-christmas-winner-sales-clothing-retailer\" title=\"\">enjoyed strong Christmas sales</a>.</p><p>The BRC said weak trading performance in the lead-up to Christmas led to \"above-normal levels of promotional activity\" and that although inflationary pressure in the supply chain remains benign, \"deep and widespread discounts have come at the expenses of profit margins\".</p><p>But the lobby group sought to emphasise the benefits for shoppers grappling with falling real wages as average pay rises fail to match inflation.</p><p>\"This is the deepest deflation rate since we started compiling the index in 2006, and the eighth consecutive month of falling shop prices. That's a double whammy of good news for cash-conscious customers, and confirms our predictions that retailers worked hard to help budgets go that bit further this Christmas,\" said BRC director general Helen Dickinson.</p><p>She pointed out that the day dubbed \"Cyber Monday\" by retailers, said to be the busiest online shopping day of the year, fell within the latest set of figures. Although the BRC/Nielsen data does not cover online prices the group said a number of retailers ran similar promotions in-store.</p><p>The discounts in December appeared to be deepest in clothing and footwear, with prices down 9.9% on the year. Electricals were down 3.5%, furniture prices fell 1.7% and the books, stationery and home entertainment category slipped into deflationary territory with prices down 1.4%. In DIY and in health and beauty prices were up but at a slower pace and in the \"other non-food\" category inflation held steady.</p>","headline":"Shop prices fall at fastest pace in seven years in December","trailText":"Retailers using deep discounts to attract cash-strapped consumers, the British Retail Consortium says","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3yk7y","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/1/7/1389112519935/Sale-promotions-004.jpg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/1/7/1389112519935/Sale-promotions-004.jpg","wordcount":"467","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"426505612","allowUgc":"false","internalOctopusCode":"8524598","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Katie Allen","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-01-08T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2022456","productionOffice":"